Package com.salesforce.multicloudj.pubsub.client

Class SubscriptionClient

java.lang.Object
com.salesforce.multicloudj.pubsub.client.SubscriptionClient
All Implemented Interfaces:
AutoCloseable
public class SubscriptionClient extends Object implements AutoCloseable
High-level client for receiving messages from a pubsub subscription. SubscriptionClient provides a simplified interface for receiving messages from cloud pubsub services in a provider-agnostic way. It handles batching, acknowledgments, and error conversion automatically.

    • sendAck

      public void sendAck(AckID ackID)
      Acknowledges a single message, indicating successful processing. Acknowledged messages will not be redelivered. The acknowledgment is sent asynchronously in the background.
      Parameters:
      ackID - The acknowledgment ID of the message to acknowledge
      Throws:
      SubstrateSdkException - If the ack operation fails

    • sendAcks

      public CompletableFuture<Void> sendAcks(List<AckID> ackIDs)
      Acknowledges multiple messages in a batch. This is more efficient than calling sendAck multiple times. Acknowledged messages will not be redelivered.
      Parameters:
      ackIDs - The list of acknowledgment IDs to acknowledge
      Returns:
      A CompletableFuture that completes when all acks are sent

    • sendNack

      public void sendNack(AckID ackID)
      Negatively acknowledges a single message, indicating processing failure. Nacked messages will be redelivered for retry. Not all providers support nacking - check canNack() first.
      Parameters:
      ackID - The acknowledgment ID of the message to nack
      Throws:
      SubstrateSdkException - If the nack operation fails
      UnsupportedOperationException - If the provider doesn't support nacking

    • sendNacks

      public CompletableFuture<Void> sendNacks(List<AckID> ackIDs)
      Negatively acknowledges multiple messages in a batch. This is more efficient than calling sendNack multiple times. Nacked messages will be redelivered for retry.
      Parameters:
      ackIDs - The list of acknowledgment IDs to nack
      Returns:
      A CompletableFuture that completes when all nacks are sent
      Throws:
      UnsupportedOperationException - If the provider doesn't support nacking

    • canNack
